Wharf Rat:<br><br>
When my kids torque me up... do the wrong stuff... piss me off...etc.  I come down on their behavior and not them.  We have a lot in common... and I love them &quot;no matter what!&quot;<br><br>
Cook is my blood brother... not because of the blood that runs in our veins... but because of the blood that ran on the ground.  He is family.  Maybe I could get angry with what he says or does... but never at him.  I would die for him at the drop of a hat.<br><br>
Doctor Barry Spatz, you are my family too!  I may view you as the &quot;Black Sheep&quot; and you may call me the &quot;Ugly Duckling,&quot; but that is allowed in family disputes.  Some ideas you have make sense... some I find revolting. Cook and I both would die for you... we demonstrated that a long time ago.<br><br>
You can't save the whales... can't save the gooks... can't save the soldiers... can't save the rivers!  You're lucky if you can save five dollars.  Better yet, you're damned lucky if you can save yourself.<br><br>
Try a tentative style of confrontation with your brothers.  They may not reciprocate... but you will come away cleaner.<br><br>
Your Idol, Hero and Principle Significant Other,<br><br>
Field Rat Six<br><br>
P.S.  Pee Wee Herman turned down the opportunity to play your part in Cook's upcoming movie extravaganza... there was some kind of drivel that he had a reputation to protect&lt;G&gt;.
